<br>
You said that they were so insanely good at what they do that they trivialize some small group encounters. That's what the statement you said read as. I don't consider that trivializing anything. Though, if by trivialize you mean 'makes it far easier than without', then heck, Magicians trivialize many encounters just as they are. I've been in many fights where without the damage output of my pet and the ability to ping pong aggro from pet to pet (multiple pet groups/raids), things would've been very bad. Magicians with CotH can trivialize just about any locked dungeon except for Luclin ones. So long as you don't have to cross a zone line for the second half of that zone, we magicians can trivialize it. That's why they sought to nerf CotH in Luclin zones, you know.<br>
<br>
Anyways, perhaps if you state clearer more what you intend to say, there might be less cause to pick holes in what you say. <p><A HREF="http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=52886">Rhasin Firestorm</A><BR>
